==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: man-of-the-earth
<hw>man-of-the-earth</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A long-rooted morning glory (<spn>Ipomoea leptophylla</spn>) of
Western U. S.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> man of the earth, <spn>Ipomoea
leptophylla</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A tropical American prostrate or climbing herbaceous
perennial (<spn>Ipomoea panurata</spn> or <spn>Ipomoea fastigiata</spn>)
having an enormous starchy root; sometimes held to be source of the
sweet potato.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> wild potato vine, wild sweet potato vine, man of the
earth, manroot, scammonyroot, <spn>Ipomoea panurata</spn>, <spn>Ipomoea
fastigiata</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>man of the world</ent>⟦br⟧
